@startuml 07-component-diagram
' CVerify — Component diagram with provided/required interfaces and real protocols
' Verified against:
'   docker-compose.yml · deployment/docker-compose.prod.yml · deployment/nginx/cverify.conf
'   CVerify.Core/Program.cs                                  (AiServiceClient named HttpClient, SignalR hubs,
'                                                             Redis, S3 client via R2_* keys)
'   CVerify.Core/Modules/Shared/Hubs/                        (NotificationHub) · Modules/Admin/Hubs/ (AdminHub)
'   CVerify.Core/Modules/Auth/Controllers/AuthController.cs:520,529,634,672,696
'   CVerify.Core/Modules/Auth/Services/AuthService.cs:1892,1897,1963,1984,2707-2734 (VietQR named client)
'   CVerify.Core/appsettings.json:33                          (SendGrid section)
'   CVerify.AI/app/main.py:152,165,214                        (router include, /health, /api/v1/chat/stream)
'   CVerify.AI/app/api/routes/analysis_router.py:55-406       (9 routed endpoints)
'   CVerify.AI/app/core/middleware/hmac_auth.py
'   CVerify.AI/app/pipelines/{repository,candidate,jd,requirement}/
'   docs/architecture/reverse-engineered/GROUND-TRUTH.md  §1, §5, §5.3, §6

title CVerify — Component Diagram (interfaces and protocols as implemented)

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Browser user" as U

component "Next.js Client\n(cverify-client)" as CLIENT
component "nginx\n(host-installed)" as NGINX

component "Core API — cverify-core\nASP.NET Core .NET 10 modular monolith" as CORE {
  component "Auth" as M_AUTH
  component "Profiles" as M_PROF
  component "SourceCode" as M_SRC
  component "Recovery" as M_REC
  component "Forum" as M_FORUM
  component "AiChat" as M_CHAT
  component "Admin" as M_ADMIN
  component "Intelligence" as M_INTEL
  component "Shared" as M_SHARED
}

component "AI Service — cverify-ai\nFastAPI · Python 3.11" as AI {
  component "Line 1 — Repository pipeline\ngithub_analysis_orchestrator.py\n22 tasks, flat if/elif dispatcher" as P1
  component "Line 2 — Candidate pipeline\n16-task validated DAG (cycle-checked)" as P2
  component "Line 3 — JD matching\n13 standalone tasks, no DAG" as P3
  component "Line 4 — Requirement artifacts\n1 Claude call -> 5 artifacts" as P4
}

database "PostgreSQL 16\npgvector image" as PG
database "Redis 7.2.4" as REDIS
node "MinIO\n(S3-compatible)" as MINIO

cloud "Anthropic Claude API" as CLAUDE
cloud "GitHub\n(OAuth + REST)" as GH
cloud "GitLab\n(OAuth + REST v4)" as GL
cloud "Google OAuth 2.0" as GOOG
cloud "VietQR\nbusiness registry" as VQR
cloud "SMTP / SendGrid" as MAIL

' ---- provided / required interfaces ----------------------------------------
interface "HTTPS :443" as I_HTTPS
interface "SSE\ntext/event-stream" as I_SSE
interface "SignalR\nWebSocket" as I_WS
interface "HMAC-signed HTTP\n(X-Signature, X-Client-Id,\nX-Timestamp, X-Nonce,\nX-Correlation-Id)" as I_HMAC
interface "Redis pub/sub\n+ key/value" as I_REDIS
interface "S3 API\nForcePathStyle=true" as I_S3
interface "Npgsql / EF Core" as I_PG

U --> CLIENT
CLIENT --> I_HTTPS
I_HTTPS -- NGINX
NGINX --> CORE : proxy_pass\n127.0.0.1:5247
NGINX --> CLIENT : proxy_pass\n127.0.0.1:3000

CORE -up- I_SSE
CLIENT --> I_SSE : 5 SSE endpoints
note right of I_SSE
  POST api/ai/chat/stream
  GET  api/v1/candidate-assessments/progress/{userId}
  GET  api/v1/hiring-requirements/{id}/progress-stream
  GET  api/v1/streaming/sessions/{id}/progress-stream
  GET  api/repository-analyses/jobs/{jobId}/progress-stream
  ⚠ nginx SSE regex coverage of all 5 is <<Not verified>>.
end note

CORE -up- I_WS
CLIENT --> I_WS : /hubs/notifications, /hubs/admin
note right of I_WS
  NotificationHub — no groups, no client-invokable methods.
  AdminHub — group "admins", gated on SUPER_ADMIN/ADMIN.
  Fan-out is Redis pub/sub channel "cverify:notifications".
end note

CORE --> I_HMAC
I_HMAC -- AI
note bottom of I_HMAC
  Named HttpClient "AiServiceClient", 5-minute timeout.
  HMACSHA256(METHOD + URL + BODY + TIMESTAMP + NONCE, SharedSecret).
  8 endpoints called: /chat/stream, /repository/assess,
  /candidate/assess/stream, /candidate/assess/score,
  /hiring-requirements/generate/stream,
  /hiring-requirements/generate-artifact/stream,
  /analysis/task/execute, /analysis/task/aggregate.
  ⚠ POST /api/v1/analysis/jobs/{job_id}/cancel has NO HMAC guard.
end note

AI --> CORE : callback (HTTP)\nGET api/v1/ai-jobs/{jobId}/artifacts/{key}
note on link
  Class-level [AllowAnonymous]; comment says
  "allow internal microservice to call without bearer auth".
  Any in-body guard is <<Not verified>>.
end note

CORE --> I_PG
I_PG -- PG
CORE --> I_REDIS
AI --> I_REDIS : cancellation poll ai:cancel:{correlation_id}
I_REDIS -- REDIS
CORE --> I_S3
I_S3 -- MINIO
note right of I_S3
  Env keys keep R2_* names because the S3 client is generic.
  Cloudflare R2 is supported by the same client but MinIO is
  what is deployed.
end note

AI --> CLAUDE : HTTPS, stream=True, max_tokens=8192\nprompt caching cache_control: ephemeral
note right of CLAUDE
  Default model claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022.
  Only other model: hardcoded claude-3-haiku-20240307
  for vision OCR (gated OFF by default).
end note

AI --> GH : git clone over HTTPS\n⚠ clone URL embeds the PAT
M_AUTH --> GH  : OAuth 2.0 + api.github.com/user
M_AUTH --> GL  : OAuth 2.0 + gitlab.com/api/v4/user
M_AUTH --> GOOG: OAuth 2.0 (accounts.google.com)
M_AUTH --> VQR : HTTPS, named client "VietQR"\n(tax-code lookup, retry w/ backoff)
M_SHARED --> MAIL : SMTP or SendGrid\n(EmailSettings__Provider)

note bottom of AI
  ⚠ Absent despite the documented claim: OCR/text-extraction modules
  (dead code), embedding module (pruned), SFIA levels, O*NET lookup.
  ⚠ prompt_sanitizer.py / malicious_repo_detector.py /
  input_boundary.validate_token_count are stubs and imported nowhere.
end note

note bottom of CORE
  9 modules. Boundaries enforced by
  tests/CVerify.API.UnitTests/Architecture/ModularBoundaryTests.cs.
  ⚠ CORS "AllowFrontend" hardcodes http://localhost:3000 and
  http://127.0.0.1:3000 in ALL environments including Production.
end note

@enduml
